Blockchain
Searching Large Data
Advantages
Very fast searching
Fast insertion
Fast deletion
Efficient for large datasets
Simple to use with hash maps and hash sets
Disadvantages
Collisions can occur
Performance depends on a good hash function
Extra memory may be needed
Worst-case performance can become O(n)
Key Points to Remember
Hashing stores data for fast access.
A Hash Function converts a key into an index.
A Hash Table stores data at that index.
A Collision occurs when two keys map to the same index.
Collisions are handled using Separate Chaining or Open Addressing.
Load Factor measures how full the hash table is.
Rehashing creates a larger table when needed.
Average time complexity for Search, Insert, and Delete is O(1).
